{"key":"post-15972498","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15972498</id>\n<content>You should use the grains as grains and simply inoculate with them.&amp;nbsp; Making grain LC adds another vector of contamination with no corresponding benefit.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Many species can be used to colonize a grain jar, and then frozen solid until needed.&amp;nbsp; I have several species which have been frozen for nearly five years this way and are still viable. &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15972602</next>\n<prev>15972235</prev>\n<first>15960471</first>\n<last>15977065</last>\n<when>1332281282</when>\n<utime>03/21/12 01:08 AM</utime>\n</post>"}